Key Match Events: Netherlands won by 6 wickets (with 8 balls remaining)
Aasif Sheikh was dismissed by Pringle in the second over
Kushal Bhurtel was dismissed by van Beek with his first ball
Vivian Kingma found big movement as the Nepal batters found putting bat to ball an arduous task
Sompal Kami got rid of Michael Levitt with his second ball
Vikramjit Singh was taken out by Airee with a length ball that beat the batter's attempted slog sweep and caught him in front
Max O'Dowd reached his 13th T20I fifty
Post-Match Reflections: Netherlands' depth of seam-bowling challenged Nepal
Nepal's players appreciated the lively support they got in Dallas
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Grand Prairie Stadium can seat 7000 but the vocal Nepal fans made it feel a lot bigger, flocking in nice and early getting behind their team
Early-morning rain and overcast conditions delayed the toss by 30 minutes
Others: Rohit Paudel, the youngest captain at a T20 World Cup at 21
Karan KC and Gulsan Jha added 22 off 17 balls for the eighth wicket - the second-highest stand of the innings
Abinash Bohara ended the innings with a two-in-two
Tim Pringle, Logan van Beek, Paul van Meekeren and Bas de Leede all got among the wickets
Sybrand Engelbrecht tried to steady to ship in a 28-run stand before a run out brought about the latter's end
When Netherlands required 13 off 12, O'Dowd smashed Abinash Bohara for a four and six to reach his 13th T20I fifty
De Leede then finished the chase with a four through covers, triggering a sigh of relief in the Netherlands camp and securing two crucial points
